138
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:14,583
[DAD] You know what it was?

139
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:17,541
You probably got
saved by a mermaid.

140
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,375
A mermaid?

141
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:23,125
[DAD] I was
being sarcastic, son.

142
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:25,708
You were just
dreaming. Let's go.

143
00:08:25,791 --> 00:08:28,791
[DAD] I don't wanna catch
a cold on our vacation.

144
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:30,250
[NAGASUMI]
Hey! Dad!

145
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,666
I'm not making this up!
I really did drown!

146
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:35,000
I'm being serious here!
Hey, Dad!

147
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:37,166
C'mon!
Listen to me!

148
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,458
[grandmother laughs]

149
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:41,708
[GRANDMOTHER] So Nagasumi.

150
00:08:41,791 --> 00:08:43,791
Ya got saved by a pretty
little mermaid, did ya?

151
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:46,416
It's true, Grandma!
I saw her!

152
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:47,875
Will you give
it a rest already?

153
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:50,541
You're embarrassing me!
How did you end up like this?

154
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:52,750
[NAGASUMI] I don't know,
but I blame my parents.

155
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,458
I guess there aren't any
mermaids in Saitama, are there?

156
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:56,583
That's sweet,
but you don't

157
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:57,791
have to humor him,
Grandma.

158
00:08:57,875 --> 00:09:00,041
I swear to you
that I'm not making this up!

159
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:02,083
I can't count the
legends I've heard

160
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:04,708
about mermaids in
the Seto Inland Sea.

161
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:07,416
People are always claiming
to see them in these parts.

162
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,125
Do they really?

163
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:12,958
And ya just better hope
the legends aren't true.

164
00:09:13,041 --> 00:09:15,833
Or else you're gonna be
in a whole heap of trouble.

165
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,833
What do you
mean by trouble?

166
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:19,250
C'mon, mom.

167
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,416
He was just dreaming.
I found him asleep on the beach.

168
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,583
It wasn't a dream!

169
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:24,333
I don't know where
he gets this stuff from.

170
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:25,875
You raised me, didn't you?

171
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,416
Just let me describe
her for you, okay?

172
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,833
She had this long,

173
